            <span id="ChapterParagraphTwo">
                Kenneth was always supportive, and he was very anxious for our children to learn to work. Even from the very beginning, our boys were taught how to work and to take responsibility to help with the family.<br /><br />

                Kenneth was an excellent farmer. He was honest in his dealings with his fellow men, which was very important to me. He would always plan for the future and was quite successful in farming. At one time he was nominated to be the recipient of Outstanding Young Farmer in Bonneville County because he was such a hard worker and had a good farm.
            </span>
            <!--span id="SEE_MORE"><a href="#" id="restofstory4-show"  onclick="showHide('restofstory4');return false;">SEE MORE</a>
