                <span id="ChapterParagraphTwo">
                    As we began to date, I could see the qualities in Kenneth. He was extremely handsome. He was a handsome young man. In fact, as his granddaughters have seen pictures of him, they’ve said, “Oh my goodness, Grandma. He was a hottie,“ in the modern vernacular. Not only that, but he had a very strong testimony of the gospel; he wanted to be married and sealed in the temple, and he wanted a home and a family. 

                    Kenneth already had an 80-acre farm with a lovely home. He hadn’t lived in the home. The home had been used by other members of the family as they lived out there, but it was a lovely home in Milo. He was ready to settle, I knew that he was a hard worker, and I knew that he was honest and had integrity. 

                    He was a really good dancer, as well. We had a lot of fun at the dances during our courtship.
